<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="230" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,987,1372]" pageId="9" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1095,1120]" pageId="9" pageNumber="230">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet taken from the Latin 
<taxonomicName box="[808,867,1096,1119]" class="Insecta" family="Chyromyidae" genus="Aphaniosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="230" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="soror">
<emphasis box="[808,867,1096,1119]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="230">soror</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, meaning sister, refers to the marked similarity of this species to 
<taxonomicName authority="Ebejer, 2006" authorityName="Ebejer" authorityYear="2006" box="[315,576,1131,1156]" class="Insecta" family="Chyromyidae" genus="Aphaniosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="230" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis box="[315,427,1131,1156]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="230">A. subtilis</emphasis>
Ebejer, 2006
</taxonomicName>
described from Kyrgizstan.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
